underlying_goal: To explore options for making the `auto_log.sh` command log more useful and searchable.
primary_success: Proposing a dual-logging strategy (human-readable .log and structured .jsonl) as a solution to the user's conflicting requirements for scannability and programmatic queryability.
brief_summary: The user asked for recommendations to make their command logs more searchable. Claude proposed several options, leading to a discussion on the trade-offs between human-readable and machine-readable (JSONL) formats. The session ended as they converged on a dual-log strategy.
